Tepco’s Shimizu Tells Japanese Lawmakers He Hasn’t Decided When to Resign

-- B y   Y u j i   O k a d a
-- 
2011-04-25T04:46:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-25/tepco-s-shimizu-tells-japanese-lawmakers-he-hasn-t-decided-when-to-resign.html
Tokyo Electric Power Co. President
Masataka Shimizu told Japanese lawmakers he hasn’t decided when
to resign to take responsbility for the crisis at the company’s
Fukushima Dai-Ichi nuclear plant. Shimizu was asked by lawmaker
Teruhiko Mashiko when he will resign while appearing today
before a budget committee of the Japanese parliament.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Yuji Okada at 
 yokada6@bloomberg.net  